July 6th, 1951, TASPO left <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../912/452912.xml">
Trinidad</link> for <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../316/9316.xml">
England</link></country>
 on the SS San Mateo. Carlton "Sonny" Roach fell ill and and was left behind in <region wordnetid="108630039" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../169/19169.xml">
Martinique</link></region>
. TASPO returned to Trinidad December 12th, 1951, the only exception being Sterling Betancourt, which stayed in London. Betancourt has been vitally involved in building up <fundamental_quantity wordnetid="113575869" confidence="0.8">
